// @run
// @log num
// @log str
// @log num
// CONTRACT: an `is` guard on an un-annotated (generic) parameter is sound. The
// parameter is NOT pinned by the guard — each call monomorphizes independently —
// and `is T` on the per-call concrete type is decided statically at codegen, so
// the right branch is taken and calls do not cross-contaminate.
function describe(x): string {
  if x is i32 { return "num" }
  return "str"
}
print(describe(5))               // num   (x is i32)
print(describe("hi"))            // str   (x is string here)
print(describe(5))               // num   (no contamination from the string call)
